# External Data Module & Table Requirements

## 1. Data Table Layout & Responsiveness
- Render external user data in a clean, responsive layout structure that eliminates layout shifts during search updates or pagination switches.
- The user table must handle high-volume text fields gracefully without breaking cell boundaries or forcing horizontal window scrolling on desktop views.

## 2. Omnibox / Global Search Functionality
- Provide a single, prominent global search input field positioned directly above the data table.
- **Fuzzy Matching:** The global search must evaluate queries against all text-based attributes simultaneously (e.g., searching "John" scans First Name, Last Name, Email, and Department).
- Provide instant visual feedback if a search yields zero results, displaying a clear "No users found matching your criteria" message within a responsive Bootstrap component container.

## 3. Column-Level Filtering
- Each searchable data column (e.g., Name, Email, Role, Status) must include its own individual, context-aware filter control located directly inside or immediately below the column header.
- **Filter Mechanics:** 
  - Text columns (Name/Email) must support partial match input text fields.
  - Categorical columns (Role/Status) must utilize drop-down selectors listing unique values.
- **Combined Search Logic:** Column-level filters must act as logical `AND` constraints alongside the global search field (e.g., Global search = "Smith" `AND` Column Role Filter = "Faculty").